    "These reactions are crucial for pollutant degradation and hydrogen production.",
    "The interaction of thiazine dye-sensitized TiO 2 with target molecules or pollutants on the surface is essential for the photocatalytic process (Zani et al., 2021; Senthilkumar et al., 2010; Barakat et al., 2022).",
    "Surface adsorption, electron transfer, and radical reactions play a significant role in the degradation or transformation of target compounds.",
    "Researchers often study the quantum yields of photocatalytic reactions to understand the efficiency of the process.",
